ven by strong current densities up to the depairing limit at low\ntemperatures. The behavior of $R_i(H)$ which can be tuned by varying the rf\nfrequency or concentration of nonmagnetic impurities is not masked by strong\nheating effects characteristic of dc or pulse transport measurements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Jan 2020 22:32:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-06"}
